main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported over San Jose and Alameda, California, on February 7, 1950.
interesting points: One sighting was described as a 'flying ice cream cone,' observed drifting over Alameda Naval Air Station., Eyewitnesses reported the object trailing a gray parachute., Multiple military and civilian witnesses reported the object with varying descriptions and characteristics., Reports included claims of speed estimates up to 1500 MPH and altitudes of 600 feet., There were no photographs available in the reports.
sighted object: circular object and ice cream cone shape
witness description: Army & Navy officers, civilians, and passengers on a train.
